{"questionId":"9076727","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A planet has radius <em>R</em>. At a distance <em>h </em>above the surface of the planet the&nbsp;gravitational field strength is <em>g </em>and the gravitational potential is <em>V</em>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Show that <em>V </em>= –<em>g</em>(<em>R </em>+ <em>h</em>).</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>at height <em>h </em>potential is&nbsp;<em>V</em> = –<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{GM}}{{(R + h)}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>G</mi>\n      <mi>M</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n      <mi>R</mi>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mi>h</mi>\n      <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>field is <em>g </em>=&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{GM}}{{{{(R + h)}^2}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>G</mi>\n      <mi>M</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n            <mi>R</mi>\n            <mo>+</mo>\n            <mi>h</mi>\n            <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><strong>«</strong>dividing gives answer<strong>»</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Do not allow an answer that starts with g = –</em><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{\\Delta V}}{{\\Delta r}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi>\n      <mi>V</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi>\n      <mi>r</mi>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span><em> and then cancels the deltas and substitutes </em><em>R </em>+ <em>h</em></p>\n<p><strong><em>[2 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9076727","referenceCode":"18M.2.HL.TZ2.a.ii","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Show that V = –g(R + h).","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 10: Fields","10.1 – Describing fields","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 10: Fields"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}